A LARGE COMPLEX AREA OF LOW PRESSURE LIES SITUATED OVER THE EERN ATLANTIC
TO THE SW OF ICELAND WEDNESDAY EVENING 975 AND DRIFTS SLWY N AND E WHILST
FLN THROUGHOUT THE PERIOD. THIS IS EXP TO PUSH FRONTAL SYSTEMS N AND EWARDS
ACROSS THE UK DURING THE LATTER PART OF THE WEEK. MEANWHILE THE AZORES HIGH
LOOKS TO LOOKS TO BUILD A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE ACROSS FITZROY AT TIMES
FORMING A HIGH PRESSURE 1022 ACROSS THE ENGLISH CHANNEL THROUGH THURSDAY
WHICH IS LIKELY TO EXTEND ACROSS THE SERN HALF OF THE UK BEFORE CLEARING
E INTO FRIDAY TO ALLOW A SHALLOW LOW TO MOV UP FM THE NEAR CONTINENT INTO
